
"smart_sources:_000.General/\"It is not necessary to change a person in order to change their behavior. Just change their environment.\".md": {"path":"_000.General/\"It is not necessary to change a person in order to change their behavior. Just change their environment.\".md","last_embed":{"hash":null},"embeddings":{},"last_read":{"hash":"1mcrqwe","at":1772113914192},"class_name":"SmartSource","last_import":{"mtime":1760197808000,"size":1216,"at":1772113914193,"hash":"1mcrqwe"},"blocks":{"#":[1,4],"##{1}":[1,1],"##{2}":[2,2],"##{3}":[3,4],"##Highlights":[5,16],"##Highlights#{1}":[6,7],"##Highlights#{2}":[8,10],"##Highlights##[[“It’s easier to practice self-restraint when you don’t have to use it.\"]]: “Our prototypical model of self-control is angel on one side and devil on the other, and they battle it out. . . . We tend to think of people with strong willpower as people who are able to fight this battle effectively. Actually, the people who are really good at self-control never have these battles in the first place.” For more, see Brian Resnick, “The Myth of Self-Control,” Vox, November 24, 2016, https://www.vox.com/science-and-health/2016/11/3/13486940/self-control-psychology-myth.”":[11,16],"##Highlights##[[“It’s easier to practice self-restraint when you don’t have to use it.\"]]: “Our prototypical model of self-control is angel on one side and devil on the other, and they battle it out. . . . We tend to think of people with strong willpower as people who are able to fight this battle effectively. Actually, the people who are really good at self-control never have these battles in the first place.” For more, see Brian Resnick, “The Myth of Self-Control,” Vox, November 24, 2016, https://www.vox.com/science-and-health/2016/11/3/13486940/self-control-psychology-myth.”#{1}":[13,16]},"outlinks":[{"title":"James Clear","target":"James Clear","line":1},{"title":"Atomic Habits","target":"Atomic Habits","line":2},{"title":"Leadership","target":"Leadership","line":2},{"title":"Learning MOC","target":"Learning MOC","line":2},{"title":"MOC Habits","target":"MOC Habits","line":2},{"title":"Parenting","target":"Parenting","line":2},{"title":"People","target":"People","line":2},{"title":"Remove obstructions and make easier to do the right thing, habit.#^387ab2","target":"Remove obstructions and make easier to do the right thing, habit.#^387ab2","line":8,"embedded":true},{"title":"The Myth of Self-Control#^d2249f","target":"The Myth of Self-Control#^d2249f","line":10,"embedded":true},{"title":"“It’s easier to practice self-restraint when you don’t have to use it.\"","target":"“It’s easier to practice self-restraint when you don’t have to use it.\"","line":11},{"title":"“To know your Enemy, you must become your Enemy.”    ― Sun Tzu","target":"“To know your Enemy, you must become your Enemy.”    ― Sun Tzu","line":13},{"title":"The greatest victory is that which requires no battle.”  ― Sun Tzu, The Art of War","target":"The greatest victory is that which requires no battle.”  ― Sun Tzu, The Art of War","line":15}],"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},
